content.text: Which arrow points to a hydrogen bond? <image 1>

The arrow labeled "c" points to a hydrogen bond in the image. Hydrogen bonds are represented by dashed lines between the hydrogen atom of one molecule and the oxygen atom of another molecule. In this case, the dashed line between the hydrogen atom of one water molecule and the oxygen atom of another water molecule indicates a hydrogen bond.
